[2026-03-07T17:01:19Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012pjsYozehXMDChYCbrvGaP","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package grpc_test\n     2→\n     3→import (\n     4→\t\"context\"\n     5→\t\"encoding/json\"\n     6→\t\"fmt\"\n     7→\t\"os\"\n     8→\t\"path/filepath\"\n     9→\t\"sync/atomic\"\n    10→\t\"testing\"\n    11→\t\"time\"\n    12→\n    13→\tpb \"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/api/clochepb\"\n    14→\tserver \"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/adapters/grpc\"\n    15→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/adapters/local\"\n    16→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/adapters/sqlite\"\n    17→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/domain\"\n    18→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/protocol\"\n    19→\t\"github.com/stretchr/testify/assert\"\n    20→\t\"github.com/stretchr/testify/require\"\n    21→\tgrpclib \"google.golang.org/grpc\"\n    22→)\n    23→\n    24→func TestServer_ListRuns_Empty(t *testing.T) {\n    25→\tstore, err := sqlite.NewStore(\":memory:\")\n    26→\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n    27→\tdefer store.Close()\n    28→\n    29→\tsrv := server.NewClocheServer(store, nil)\n    30→\tresp, err := srv.ListRuns(context.Background(), &pb.ListRunsRequest{All: true})\n    31→\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n    32→\tassert.Empty(t, resp.Runs)\n    33→}\n    34→\n    35→func TestServer_GetStatus_NotFound(t *testing.T) {\n    36→\tstore, err := sqlite.NewStore(\":memory:\")\n    37→\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n    38→\tdefer store.Close()\n    39→\n    40→\tsrv := server.NewClocheServer(store, nil)\n    41→\t_, err = srv.GetStatus(context.Background(), &pb.GetStatusRequest{RunId: \"nonexistent\"})\n    42→\tassert.Error(t, err)\n    43→}\n    44→\n    45→func TestServer_RunWorkflow(t *testing.T) {\n    46→\tstore, err := sqlite.NewStore(\":memory:\")\n    47→\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n    48→\tdefer store.Close()\n    49→\n    50→\tdir := t.TempDir()\n    51→\n    52→\t// Create a mock \"agent\" shell script at test.cloche that outputs JSON status lines.\n    53→\t// The local runtime runs: sh <projectDir>/test.cloche\n    54→\tmsgs := []protocol.StatusMessage{\n    55→\t\t{Type: protocol.MsgStepStarted, StepName: \"build\"},\n    56→\t\t{Type: protocol.MsgStepCompleted, StepName: \"build\", Result: \"success\"},\n    57→\t\t{Type: protocol.MsgRunCompleted, Result: \"succeeded\"},\n    58→\t}\n    59→\tscript := \"#!/bin/sh\\n\"\n    60→\tfor _, msg := range msgs {\n    61→\t\tdata, _ := json.Marshal(msg)\n    62→\t\tscript += \"echo '\" + string(data) + \"'\\n\"\n    63→\t}\n    64→\trequire.NoError(t, os.MkdirAll(filepath.Join(dir, \".cloche\"), 0755))\n    65→\trequire.NoError(t, os.WriteFile(filepath.Join(dir, \".cloche\", \"test.cloche\"), []byte(script), 0755))\n    66→\n    67→\t// Use \"sh\" as the agent binary so it runs: sh test.cloche\n    68→\trt := local.NewRuntime(\"sh\")\n    69→\tsrv := server.NewClocheServerWithCaptures(store, store, rt, \"\")\n    70→\n    71→\tresp, err := srv.RunWorkflow(context.Background(), &pb.RunWorkflowRequest{\n    72→\t\tWorkflowName: \"test\",\n    73→\t\tProjectDir:   dir,\n    74→\t\tPrompt:       \"hello world\",\n    75→\t})\n    76→\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n    77→\tassert.NotEmpty(t, resp.RunId)\n    78→\n    79→\t// Verify prompt was written to run-specific path\n    80→\tpromptData, err := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(dir, \".cloche\", resp.RunId, \"prompt.txt\"))\n    81→\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n    82→\tassert.Equal(t, \"hello world\", string(promptData))\n    83→\n    84→\t// Poll until the background goroutine finishes processing (up to 5s)\n    85→\tvar status *pb.GetStatusResponse\n    86→\tdeadline := time.Now().Add(5 * time.Second)\n    87→\tfor time.Now().Before(deadline) {\n    88→\t\tstatus, err = srv.GetStatus(context.Background(), &pb.GetStatusRequest{RunId: resp.RunId})\n    89→\t\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n    90→\t\tif status.State == \"succeeded\" && len(status.StepExecutions) >= 1 {\n    91→\t\t\tbreak\n    92→\t\t}\n    93→\t\ttime.Sleep(50 * time.Millisecond)\n    94→\t}\n    95→\n    96→\t// Check that the run was tracked and completed\n    97→\trequire.NotNil(t, status)\n    98→\tassert.Equal(t, resp.RunId, status.RunId)\n    99→\tassert.Equal(t, \"succeeded\", status.State)\n   100→\tassert.GreaterOrEqual(t, len(status.StepExecutions), 1)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01DJNKvD94FQN8XnRkcUqQy8","session_id":"ecf2254e-a4f5-42ab-a6c8-02074c39afa3","uuid":"18117202-4cc2-4d4f-bfec-accf029a1f05"}
[2026-03-07T17:01:19Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DJNKvD94FQN8XnRkcUqQy8","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile the comprehensive report:\n\n## Comprehensive Report: Container Image Building and Workflow Launch\n\nI've thoroughly searched the Cloche codebase to understand container image building and workflow launch processes. Here are the key findings:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Daemon's RunWorkflow Handler/Service Method**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`  \n**Lines:** 96-143\n\nThe `RunWorkflow` RPC handler:\n- **Signature:** `func (s *ClocheServer) RunWorkflow(ctx context.Context, req *pb.RunWorkflowRequest) (*pb.RunWorkflowResponse, error)`\n- **Behavior:**\n  - Generates a unique run ID (with collision retry)\n  - Writes the prompt to `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`\n  - Creates a Run record in the store (state = pending)\n  - **Launches container in background** via `go s.launchAndTrack()` so the RPC returns immediately\n  - Returns the runID to the client\n\n**Launch Phase:** Lines 148-196 (`launchAndTrack` method)\n- Calls `EnsureImage()` if the runtime supports it (Docker does)\n- Gets git HEAD SHA at request time\n- Calls `container.Start()` to spawn the container\n- Records container ID in the run record\n- Spawns background goroutine `trackRun()` to monitor container\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Container Image Building Logic**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/build.go`  \n**Lines:** 20-188\n\n**Key Function:** `EnsureImage(ctx, projectDir, image string) error`\n- **Called From:** `launchAndTrack()` at `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go:152-161`\n- **Behavior:**\n  1. Reads `.cloche/Dockerfile` from the project directory\n  2. If no Dockerfile exists, returns nil (nothing to validate)\n  3. Computes SHA256 hash of the Dockerfile content\n  4. Checks if image exists and reads the `cloche.dockerfile.hash` label\n  5. If image missing OR hash mismatch, calls `buildImage()`\n  6. **Staleness Check:** Also detects if the base image (FROM directive) has changed locally by comparing stored digest label\n  7. Logs decision: \"up-to-date\" or \"rebuilding\"\n\n**Docker Build Command:** Lines 160-188 (`buildImage` function)\n- Runs: `docker build -t <image> -f <dockerfile-path> --label cloche.dockerfile.hash=<hash> --label cloche.baseimage.digest=<id> <projectDir>`\n- Embeds two Docker labels:\n  - `cloche.dockerfile.hash` — SHA256 of Dockerfile content\n  - `cloche.baseimage.digest` — Image ID of the base image at build time\n- Streams build output to daemon stderr\n\n**Staleness Detection:** Lines 103-130 (`isBaseImageStale` function)\n- Parses the Dockerfile to extract the final FROM directive\n- Compares stored base image digest with current local image ID\n- Returns `(true, reason)` if stale (can trigger rebuild)\n- Gracefully degrades if label not present (old build) or base image unavailable locally\n\n---\n\n### 3. **ContainerRuntime Port/Interface**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/ports/container.go`  \n**Lines:** 24-40\n\n```go\ntype ContainerRuntime interface {\n\tStart(ctx context.Context, cfg ContainerConfig) (containerID string, err error)\n\tStop(ctx context.Context, containerID string) error\n\tAttachOutput(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (io.ReadCloser, error)\n\tWait(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (exitCode int, err error)\n\tCopyFrom(ctx context.Context, containerID string, srcPath, dstPath string) error\n\tLogs(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (string, error)\n\tRemove(ctx context.Context, containerID string) error\n\tInspect(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (*ContainerStatus, error)\n}\n\ntype ImageEnsurer interface {\n\tEnsureImage(ctx context.Context, projectDir, image string) error\n}\n```\n\n- **ImageEnsurer** is an **optional** interface; implementations register capability via type assertion\n- **ContainerConfig** fields: `Image`, `WorkflowName`, `ProjectDir`, `NetworkAllow`, `RunID`, `Cmd` (optional override)\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Existing Image Staleness & Rebuild Logic**\n\n**Two Detection Mechanisms:**\n\n1. **Dockerfile Change Detection**\n   - File: `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/build.go:35-46`\n   - Computes SHA256 hash of current Dockerfile\n   - Compares against `cloche.dockerfile.hash` label on the image\n   - Triggers rebuild if hash mismatch\n\n2. **Base Image Digest Staleness**\n   - File: `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/build.go:48-52`\n   - Parses Dockerfile for final FROM directive\n   - Reads stored `cloche.baseimage.digest` label\n   - Gets current local image ID of the base image\n   - Triggers rebuild if digests differ\n\n**Test Coverage:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/build_test.go` has comprehensive tests:\n  - `TestEnsureImage_NoDockerfile` — gracefully handles missing Dockerfile\n  - `TestEnsureImage_BuildsWhenImageMissing` — builds when image doesn't exist\n  - `TestEnsureImage_SkipsWhenUpToDate` — skips rebuild when hash matches\n  - `TestEnsureImage_RebuildsWhenDockerfileChanges` — detects Dockerfile changes\n  - `TestEnsureImage_StoresBaseImageDigest` — stores base image ID for later staleness checks\n  - `TestParseBaseImage` — handles FROM directive parsing (including multi-stage, platform flags, scratch)\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Project Dockerfile Handling**\n\n**Base Image Dockerfile:**\n- **File:** `/workspace/docker/cloche-base/Dockerfile`\n- Multi-stage build:\n  - Stage 1: Build `cloche-agent` from Go source\n  - Stage 2: debian:12-slim with cloche-agent binary, git, ca-certificates\n  - Creates non-root `agent` user\n\n**Default Project Dockerfile:**\n- **File:** `/workspace/.cloche/Dockerfile`\n- Extends `cloche-base:latest`\n- Adds Node.js/npm and Claude Code CLI\n\n**Example Project Dockerfile:**\n- **File:** `/workspace/examples/mini-redis/Dockerfile`\n- Custom dockerfile for project-specific build\n\n**Resolution Logic:**\n- **File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go:132-136`\n- Request-level override takes precedence\n- Falls back to daemon default (typically `cloche-agent:latest`)\n- Docker runtime enforces image via `ports.ContainerConfig.Image`\n\n**Dockerfile Location in Project:**\n- Must be at `<projectDir>/.cloche/Dockerfile`\n- **File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/build.go:24`\n- If absent, no build/validation occurs (success with no-op)\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Docker Runtime Implementation Details**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go`\n\n**Container Start Flow:** Lines 27-152\n1. **docker create** — Creates container with:\n   - Workdir: `/workspace`\n   - Environment: `CLOCHE_RUN_ID`, `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` (if set)\n   - Volume mounts: `CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS` (configurable)\n   - User: `root` (then chown'd to `agent` via wrapper script)\n   - Default CMD: `cloche-agent <workflow>.cloche` wrapped with chown + su\n2. **docker cp** — Copies project files into container `/workspace/`\n3. **docker cp** (overrides) — Applies files from `.cloche/overrides/` on top\n4. **docker cp** (auth) — Copies `~/.claude` and `~/.claude.json` to container\n5. **docker start** — Launches the container\n\n**Wrapper Script Logic:** Lines 82-90\n- Ensures workspace ownership by `agent` user\n- Removes Serena MCP tools (avoids onboarding overhead)\n- Strips enabled plugins from Claude settings\n- Execs to agent user: `su agent -s /bin/sh -c \"<agent-cmd>\"`\n\n**Other Methods:**\n- `AttachOutput()` — Uses `docker logs -f` to stream output\n- `Wait()` — Uses `docker wait` for exit code\n- `CopyFrom()` — Extracts files via `docker cp`\n- `Logs()` — Fetches full logs with `docker logs`\n- `Remove()` — Deletes container\n- `Inspect()` — Gets running status and exit code\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Local Runtime (Alternative)**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/local/runtime.go`\n\nFor development/testing without Docker:\n- Spawns `cloche-agent` as a local process\n- Maps `/workspace/` paths to the actual project directory\n- No image building (ImageEnsurer not implemented)\n- Used in tests (see `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server_test.go:45-101`)\n\n---\n\n### Summary Table\n\n| Component | File | Lines | Key Logic |\n|-----------|------|-------|-----------|\n| **RunWorkflow RPC** | `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` | 96-143 | Entry point, creates run, launches background container |\n| **launchAndTrack** | `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` | 148-196 | Ensures image, starts container, spawns tracking goroutine |\n| **EnsureImage** | `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/build.go` | 23-56 | Detects stale image, triggers rebuild if needed |\n| **buildImage** | `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/build.go` | 160-188 | Executes docker build with hash + base digest labels |\n| **isBaseImageStale** | `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/build.go` | 108-130 | Compares base image digest labels for staleness |\n| **ContainerRuntime** | `/workspace/internal/ports/container.go` | 24-33 | Port interface for any runtime (Docker/Local) |\n| **ImageEnsurer** | `/workspace/internal/ports/container.go` | 38-40 | Optional interface for image building |\n| **Docker Start** | `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go` | 27-152 | docker create/cp/start workflow |\n| **Local Runtime** | `/workspace/internal/adapters/local/runtime.go` | 38-72 | Spawns cloche-agent process locally |\n| **Tests** | `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/build_test.go` | 1-244 | Comprehensive staleness & build tests |"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ac3b4c82f4e5f6e81 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 49761\ntool_uses: 20\nduration_ms: 53138</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ecf2254e-a4f5-42ab-a6c8-02074c39afa3","uuid":"4237659d-0f07-4188-87ef-ef3946620443","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand how container images are