[2026-03-07T17:04:24Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014XYJ8d1ksGQHiUg9pPJZpx","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package domain\n     2→\n     3→import (\n     4→\t\"fmt\"\n     5→\t\"math/rand\"\n     6→)\n     7→\n     8→var adjectives = []string{\n     9→\t\"swift\", \"bright\", \"calm\", \"dark\", \"eager\",\n    10→\t\"fair\", \"grand\", \"happy\", \"keen\", \"lush\",\n    11→\t\"bold\", \"cool\", \"deft\", \"firm\", \"glad\",\n    12→\t\"warm\", \"wild\", \"wise\", \"crisp\", \"fresh\",\n    13→\t\"light\", \"quick\", \"sharp\", \"quiet\", \"vivid\",\n    14→\t\"brave\", \"clear\", \"gentle\", \"proud\", \"steady\",\n    15→}\n    16→\n    17→var nouns = []string{\n    18→\t\"oak\", \"elm\", \"fox\", \"hawk\", \"lake\",\n    19→\t\"pine\", \"reef\", \"sage\", \"vale\", \"wolf\",\n    20→\t\"bear\", \"cove\", \"dale\", \"fern\", \"glen\",\n    21→\t\"hare\", \"jade\", \"lark\", \"moss\", \"nest\",\n    22→\t\"peak\", \"reed\", \"star\", \"tide\", \"vine\",\n    23→\t\"birch\", \"brook\", \"crane\", \"drift\", \"flint\",\n    24→}\n    25→\n    26→// GenerateRunID produces a human-readable run ID in the format\n    27→// <workflow>-<adjective>-<noun>.\n    28→func GenerateRunID(workflowName string) string {\n    29→\tadj := adjectives[rand.Intn(len(adjectives))]\n    30→\tnoun := nouns[rand.Intn(len(nouns))]\n    31→\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"%s-%s-%s\", workflowName, adj, noun)\n    32→}\n    33→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_018B5Hj2Nng5NRAcwoSYggVk","session_id":"4b132cf9-7672-4d53-ba9d-f61c8661b9bb","uuid":"bcc3b2a7-06de-48a2-a598-d231cde10208"}
[2026-03-07T17:04:24Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018B5Hj2Nng5NRAcwoSYggVk","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a complete picture. Let me create a comprehensive summary document for the user.\n\n## Complete Flow Summary: RunWorkflow Request to Container Launch\n\nI've thoroughly analyzed the daemon's RunWorkflow handler and container image building. Here's the complete flow:\n\n### 1. **RunWorkflow RPC Handler** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`)\n\n**Entry Point:** `ClocheServer.RunWorkflow()` (lines 96-143)\n\n**Synchronous steps:**\n- Generate unique run ID using `domain.GenerateRunID(workflowName)` (format: `workflow-adjective-noun`)\n- Create `.cloche/<run-id>/` directory and write prompt to `prompt.txt` if provided\n- Create a new `Run` record in the store with state = `RunStatePending`\n- Resolve container image (request override → server default `cloche-agent:latest`)\n- Return `RunWorkflowResponse` with run ID immediately\n\n**Asynchronous launch (background goroutine):**\n- Calls `launchAndTrack()` which runs in a new background context (independent of RPC context)\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Image Ensurance** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/build.go`)\n\n**Flow:** `launchAndTrack()` → `EnsureImage()` (lines 23-56)\n\nThe Docker runtime implements optional `ImageEnsurer` interface. Before starting a container:\n\n**Image staleness check:**\n1. Read `.cloche/Dockerfile` from project\n2. Compute SHA-256 hash of file content\n3. Query `docker inspect` for `cloche.dockerfile.hash` label on built image\n4. If missing or hash mismatch → rebuild\n5. Also check base image digest:\n   - Extract `FROM` directive from Dockerfile\n   - Query current local base image ID with `docker inspect --format {{.Id}}`\n   - Compare stored `cloche.baseimage.digest` label to current ID\n   - If changed → rebuild\n\n**Image building** (lines 160-188):\n- Runs `docker build -t <image> -f <dockerfile> --label cloche.dockerfile.hash=<hash> --label cloche.baseimage.digest=<baseID> <projectDir>`\n- Streams output to daemon stderr\n- Embeds both hashes as Docker labels for future comparison\n\n**Failure handling:** If image build fails, run is marked as failed with error message\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Container Creation & File Setup** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go`)\n\n**Flow:** `launchAndTrack()` → `container.Start()` (lines 27-152)\n\n**Phase 1: Docker Create** (lines 98-105)\n- Builds `docker create` command with:\n  - Workdir: `/workspace`\n  - Default command: `cloche-agent .cloche/<workflow>.cloche` (or custom via `Cmd` override)\n  - Run ID as env var: `CLOCHE_RUN_ID=<runID>`\n  - API key passthrough: `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` (if set)\n  - Extra mounts/env from `CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS` and `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV`\n  - Default command wraps with shell script (lines 82-90) to:\n    - `chown -R agent:agent /workspace` (ownership fix)\n    - Strip `.serena` and Claude settings\n    - Execute as agent user via `su agent`\n\n**Phase 2: Copy Project Files** (lines 108-128)\n- `docker cp <projectDir>/. <containerID>:/workspace/`\n- Applies override files from `.cloche/overrides/` on top of workspace\n\n**Phase 3: Copy Claude Auth Files** (lines 131-140)\n- Copies `~/.claude` directory and `~/.claude.json` into container for agent authentication\n\n**Phase 4: Start Container** (lines 143-149)\n- `docker start <containerID>`\n- Returns container ID\n\n**Error handling:** Failures result in container cleanup and run marked as failed\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Run State Update & Tracking** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`)\n\n**Flow:** Post-launch (lines 187-195)\n- Store container ID in run record\n- Capture git HEAD SHA as `BaseSHA` for later result branch creation\n- Mark run state as `RunStateRunning`\n\n**Tracking phase** (`trackRun()`, lines 198-363):\n\n**Real-time output parsing** (lines 202-260):\n- Attach to container output via `docker logs -f <containerID>`\n- Parse JSON-lines protocol messages (from cloche-agent):\n  - `step_started`: Record step in run + captures store\n  - `step_completed`: Record result + captures store\n  - `run_completed`: Set final run state\n  - `log`: Broadcast to live-stream subscribers\n\n**Post-exit cleanup** (lines 268-357):\n1. Wait for container exit: `docker wait <containerID>`\n2. Extract step outputs: `docker cp <containerID>:/workspace/.cloche/output/. <projectDir>/.cloche/<runID>/output`\n3. Capture full logs: `docker logs <containerID>` → `container.log`\n4. Index log files in log store (full.log, llm-*.log, script logs)\n5. Trigger evolution system if configured\n6. Fire orchestrator callback if configured\n7. Extract results to git branch via `docker.ExtractResults()`:\n   - Create temp dir with `docker cp <containerID>:/workspace/. <tmpDir>/`\n   - Create git worktree at `.gitworktrees/cloche/<runID>` from `BaseSHA`\n   - Copy temp contents to worktree (excluding .git)\n   - Create branch `cloche/<runID>` and commit\n8. Container retention policy:\n   - Failed runs: always keep for debugging\n   - Successful + `--keep-container`: keep\n   - Successful + no flag: `docker rm <containerID>`\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Domain Types**\n\n**Run** (`/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`):\n- `ID`: Human-readable run ID (e.g., `develop-swift-oak`)\n- `WorkflowName`: Name of executed workflow\n- `State`: `pending|running|succeeded|failed|cancelled`\n- `ContainerID`: Docker container ID\n- `BaseSHA`: Git HEAD at run start\n- `ProjectDir`: Project root path\n- `StepExecutions`: Timeline of step start/complete events\n- `ActiveSteps`: Currently running steps\n\n**Workflow** (`/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`):\n- `Steps`: Map of step name → step definition\n- `Wiring`: List of (from_step, result) → to_step edges\n- `Collects`: Multi-condition join logic\n- `EntryStep`: First step to execute\n- `Config`: Workflow-level settings (e.g., `container.image`, `container.agent_command`)\n\n**ContainerConfig** (`/workspace/internal/ports/container.go`):\n- `Image`: Docker image name\n- `WorkflowName`: Workflow name (maps to `.cloche/<name>.cloche`)\n- `ProjectDir`: Project root for `docker cp`\n- `RunID`: Passed to container as env var\n\n**ContainerRuntime Interface**:\n- `Start()`: Create and start container\n- `Stop()`, `Wait()`, `AttachOutput()`: Lifecycle\n- `CopyFrom()`, `Remove()`: Post-run extraction\n- `Inspect()`: Health check\n- Optional `EnsureImage()`: Image validation\n\n---\n\n### 6. **In-Container Execution** (`/workspace/cmd/cloche-agent/` + `/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go`)\n\n**Container startup:** Default command `cloche-agent .cloche/<workflow>.cloche`\n\n**Agent flow:**\n1. Parse `.cloche/<workflow>.cloche` DSL file\n2. Create unified log writer at `.cloche/output/`\n3. Create execution engine with step executor\n4. Walk workflow graph via `engine.Run()`:\n   - Launch entry step\n   - Poll result channel for step completions\n   - Process wiring to determine next steps\n   - Handle fanout (parallel branches) and collects (joins)\n   - Track state transitions\n5. Emit JSON-line protocol messages on stdout:\n   - `{\"type\":\"step_started\",\"step_name\":\"...\",\"timestamp\":\"...\"}`\n   - `{\"type\":\"step_completed\",\"step_name\":\"...\",\"result\":\"...\",\"timestamp\":\"...\"}`\n   - `{\"type\":\"run_completed\",\"result\":\"succeeded|failed\",\"timestamp\":\"...\"}`\n   - `{\"type\":\"log\",\"step_name\":\"...\",\"message\":\"...\",\"timestamp\":\"...\"}`\n6. Exit with code 0 (success) or non-zero (failure)\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Key Integration Points**\n\n**Image build trigger:**\n- Before every run if `EnsureImage()` is implemented (Docker does)\n- Not implemented in local runtime\n\n**Result extraction:**\n- Happens after container exit, inside `trackRun()`\n- Creates git branch with all workspace contents\n- Used for multi-step merge workflows via orchestrator\n\n**Evolution & Orchestration:**\n- Evolution trigger fires after run completes if configured\n- Orchestrator callback fires to enable CI/CD-like chaining\n- Both receive projectDir, runID, and final state\n\n**Log indexing:**\n- Full.log captures complete run transcript\n- llm-*.log and script logs indexed separately for filtering\n- Supports real-time streaming during run execution\n\n---\n\n### **Files to Understand the Complete System:**\n\n1. `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` - RPC handlers and tracking logic\n2. `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/build.go` - Image build & staleness detection\n3. `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go` - Container lifecycle (create/start/copy)\n4. `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/extract.go` - Result extraction to git branches\n5. `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` - Run state machine\n6. `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` - Workflow validation & execution graph\n7. `/workspace/internal/ports/container.go` - ContainerRuntime interface & ImageEnsurer\n8. `/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go` - In-container workflow execution\n9. `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go` - Workflow graph execution (wiring, collects, fanout)\n10. `/workspace/internal/protocol/status.go` - JSON-line protocol messages"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a7237a90e1ee48dba (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 58950\ntool_uses: 29\nduration_ms: 98709</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4b132cf9-7672-4d53-ba9d-f61c8661b9bb","uuid":"0c3b2b61-33e4-49ff-8f98-96eb58d22cf8","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand how the daemon handles RunWorkflow requests and how container images are built. Find and read:\n\n1. The daemon's RunWorkflow handler (likely in cmd/cloched/ or internal/adapters/)\n2. The container runtime port/interface (internal/ports/)\n3. The Docker adapter that builds/runs containers (internal/adapters/docker/)\n4. Any existing image build logic\n5. The domain types for 